name: Bambini
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Had an amazing experience here. I don’t get why there any bad reviews. The food was actually AMAZING, so fresh and so good & we tried a variety of different dishes.The vibes were 10/10, service was 10/10 and the live music was beautiful. The only thing is that you can’t see the Eiffel Tower from most of the tables, only a few in a small corner offer those views for dinner. But that didn’t take away from our experience at all. We’ll definitely be back here, loved it!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The hype is real! Fantastic ambience and service. Live music and great food! The restaurant is beautiful, they have nice servers and talented artists performing. We had also a nice Eiffel Tower view. I enjoyed this place a lot. I’m picky with my Italian food, specially with tiramisù (I’d suggest to share it, it’s a huge portion for a single person). I will definitely come back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Last minute reservation made after seeing this restaurant recommend on tiktok. The pizza was big and filling, the decor and room was nice but was very pricey. Little attentions to detail such as the branded ice cube was nice. Seems to be an influencers heaven with girls taking photos with large LED lights throughout the whole night.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I had higher expectations from this restaurant. The service was unfriendly; the waitress kept mentioning how expensive it was, which I found inappropriate. A server shouldn't judge patrons based on perceived affordability; politeness should be universal. It felt like she'd only be kind if she thought you'd leave a big tip. Additionally, the food wasn't tasty.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very nice place, views and service. The best apperol spritz in paris by far and the green bean salad is a must. The food is pretty good but a bit overpriced in my opinion. Would definitely recommend for a one time ocasion.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Afrodisiac Paris 2
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Real West-African food. Very good. I have been there three times. One time, lamb. Second time fish with rice. Last time fish with banana. Very tasteful. People are very friendly.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'my boyfriend comes from Senegal and we would like to visit some nice african restaurant in Paris. After searching google we found this restaurant. Looks very sophisticated with tasteful decor.

real world was totally different.
- we had to sit very narros between other customers, event though the service person didn´t ask us whether it is fine for us.

- for washing my hands
the WC is the highlight, no sope, toilet paper around without fixing, dirty in side, smells like drain. the restaurant was not busy at all, but no one cares about it. I already lost my appetite.

- food
was not warm enough, I had seafood grill plate. the corn was bad so I spitted out and very salty.

the price range is quite high, so I would never ever visit this restaurant with that price.

Please go others.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Good food , bad service . They run out of beef and brought fish pastel to my friend without asking , not enough variety of dessert. They don’t take credit card', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great african food  the only reason why its not a 5 star is because the food is way too expensive for the small portion served. Not enough food per dish!!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food was fantastic and the staff was really helpful. Nice upscale decor.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Quai Nedy
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Best brunch in Paris

I had the Eiffel tour en plat and the blue dragon as a drink
It was incredible.
The service was also amazing,
It’s really chill chic and nice !
Highly recommend \U0001f90d', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Owner very Nice. New spot in Paris 16th facing the Eiffel tower. Cosy n warm place. Good To come with friends and better To book your table. The dishes are yummy, tasty...', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Going there for a hooka is good enough, but i do not recommend this place for the restaurant.
The food does not match with the pictures you can see online/Instagram. The avocado salad was not sliced but smashed, the multicoloured tomato salad with burrata was cold (from the fridge) and done with regular red tomatoes. The main course's portions are pretty small and not tasty for the price requested.

I was also pretty intrigued when i asked for a jug of water and the waitress told me they do not serve this kind of drink, which implies that i have to buy a bottle of water when I know its not legal to refuse tap water in restaurants in France.

I might come back for a hooka but certainly never for the restaurant.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'One of the best places I’ve ever been in paris. The food is soooooo yummy. The staff are amazingly friendly and nice. Don’t forget to try the tiramisu. It’s very delicious. And shafik is one of the best person that could attend to you. Try it you won’t regret.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Nice place near the Eiffel Tower', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Ravioli Folie
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent value for the price!  The place is beautiful, service is quick, and the food, especially the bao and shrimp bites, is really good.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was nice but the price is very expensive for the size of the portion. I would only try out the all you can eat dumpling menus because otherwise you’ll literally pay 2eur per dumpling.
This is a much more student vibe with young people than I expected so be aware if you’re thinking this will be a quiet dinner. Staff was very attentive and friendly!', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'an old waiter is so rude not welcoming us when we asked can we wait inside until opening of the restaurant, he was so indifferent and ignored us ! And the food is so normal, not fabulous but u can eat just as u want🤷‍♂️', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Tasty dumplings (ravioli)! I had pork dumplings which were fresh.

Service was attentive and kind.
Take-away logistics still require some improvement, recommend to replace the plastic boxes to paper ones to reduce waste!
Recommend, will repeat!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing food and service, highly recommend this place! Great taste and after taste :)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: YSL Cafe
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Visited this store with my family and have to say by far the best in store experience. Was served by a sales representative and he was very patient in serving us (unlike other competitors which they feel annoyed when we ask too many questions). Kudos!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Visited this store for the first time last week. This was perhaps my best in-store experience ever. Everyone was kind and knowledgeable. We felt truly welcomed. My bag from another store broke. I didn’t think anyone noticed; however, the manager offered me a bag to hold my stuff. There were multiple little things like this that occurred during our visit, that illustrated the thoughtfulness and kindness of this team.

Rim helped me and she was excellent. The person who helped my friend was also exceptional. This is the best Saint Laurent I’ve been to, and some of the best service I’ve experienced (note, there are some items that are only sold at this store). Well done Team Rive Droite! It was an absolute pleasure to visit this store.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Marieestelle- fabulous!
Excellent treatment- service - kindness and care.
What I wanted wasn’t in stock- so she arranged for same day delivery to my hotel. Followed up to make sure everything was ok, and well received. Had great knowledge of Global Blue processing… impressed', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'i have been in and out of multiple luxury shops in Paris and was treated pretty badly, probably because of how i was dressed (lol). However, i was treated exceptionally well by Lois, from the moment i stepped into YSL, despite it being very near to closing time.

Lois patiently brought out multiple bags that he thinks suit me and very nicely described each bag, yet never pushing me to purchase anything. he really wants the best for his customers and he is very sincere about it.

Thank you Lois, for the exceptional service!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I wish I could say I had a positive experience at this unique Saint Laurent location, but the way the staff treated me has left me contemplating shopping there again. I visited specifically to purchase exclusive items only available at this store, and it quickly became evident that they didn't value my business. When I requested the items I wanted to buy, the representative went to the back to retrieve them but then proceeded to assist another customer, completing their purchase and letting them leave, all while I was left waiting for my items. After nearly 20 minutes and witnessing numerous customers entering and leaving with similar items much faster, I finally received my purchases. Finally, I received my items, but the damage was done. As I was leaving, I spotted another item I wanted, and suddenly, two new representatives were all too eager to assist me, probably because it was a high-priced item. This blatant favoritism and disregard for my time and loyalty as a customer have left me seriously reconsidering whether I'll ever shop at YSL again.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: JJAN
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was very good, very close to authentic and the price for a Korean restaurant in Paris was quite “affordable”. The portions are big so it fills you well. It is a very popular restaurant so it gets crowded (even waiting lines outside) and there isn’t much space between tables. The staff is really nice and accommodating, if you need anything just ask and they will bring you.
Definitely recommend!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good Korean dishes—two pages of choices. Love my spicy tofu soup. They need more vegetarian choices. The bibimbap bowl should be much hotter as the rice was room temperature so it made the dish less exciting.  Spartan furniture.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Newly opened. Very tasty in a nicely designed restaurant.

Food wise : we got the dish to share. Cheese + chicken, some KFC as well.
It’s all good. Loved the fried chicken with their honey soy sauce.
Of course, they’ll let you take everything in takeaway if you don’t finish.

Service wise : they just opened, when it’s full it gets a bit slow but I’m sure they’ll improve very soon.

Price wise : I found it very affordable for that kind of Korean cuisine, especially considering it’s located in the very center of Paris.

I do recommend it.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great prices and great location. Small menu. We got the KFC and Budae Jigae- KFC was great and crispy and juicy. Budae came with two rice and we added spice so that was great. Nice sauce and was not too bad, 7/10. Service was quick.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Food looks delicious but is somehow tasteless.
The kimchi pancake is extra oily.
The service was nice and friendly.
Overall atmosphere is loud and fun, good for an affordable dinner with friends if you are in the area and don’t care much for the food quality.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: CÈPE ET FIGUE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We loved eating at this restaurant! I think we were lucky to get a table as it became very busy after we arrived. The food was delicious- very good quality. Even more exceptional was the service. They were very friendly and patient , despite our lack of French language skills. We later learned that it’s a family business, which just adds to the charm. Their set menu is good value for the quality of the dining experience.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent food and service. For appetizers we tried the burrata, escargots, and l’œuf cocotte - all were great. For the main dish we got L’agneau - which was cooked 7 hours and tasted sublime (although I usually don’t eat much lamb). Le poulet and le boeuf bourguignon were amazing as well. The ambience is cozy and welcoming - best to reserve a table ahead of time as it tends to be busy.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing little restaurant in St Germaine. The food is some of the best we ate in the area. The staff are all charming and helped us with the translation as the menu has some great takes on traditional French cuisine.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Easily one of the best French restaurants in Paris. The dishes and the desserts are exceptional. Very affordable price for such high quality food. I recommend!
Food ordered: comme une poule au pot, agneau, fondant au chocolat, and crumble', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Of all the times I’ve been in Paris, this is the best Parisian food I’ve had. I found this place just like that and I didn’t regret it.

Me and my husband chose the three course menu (29€ great price!) and it was just heaven. The onion soup felt like a grandma soup, the lamb was so soft and tasty and the dessert was just amazing.

Please come to this place! The food and the service is great, very very recommended.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Libshop
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'The dishes are delicious and plentiful, the service is always pleasant and efficient. One of the best places in the neighborhood for lunch, even late. I recommend !', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good Lebanese sandwich, the baked sweet potato and hummus are delicious', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I love it, the sandwiches are excellent! On the other hand, the other dishes (salad/rice) should be more garnished but otherwise good value for money for a restaurant in the 8th arrondissement!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Horrible service, the waiter doesn't understand a word of French and wanted to charge me €40 for a €10 sandwich. I wanted to cancel my order because it was impossible to communicate even that, he didn't understand it. In the end I wasted 30 minutes ending up with a sandwich with the wrong ingredients. To flee!", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "11€ for 3 falafels and green salad. Everything is bathed in an ocean of vinegar. I won't set foot there again.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: BOOM BOOM VILLETTE
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Street Banh Mi at the Food Market. Follow a very good review of Vietnamese community group on Facebook, I gave it a try to support my homeland foods and restaurant owners. I tried their special “Bánh mì chảo” which is kind of double price of a normal bánh mì 8,5€. And that’s already expensive compared to many good banh mì that I have tried in Paris. It was very noisy there and we needed to wait a bit long. And the “Bánh mì chảo” is too far from the bánh mì chảo that I know. Dry, no sauce and quantity is not up to the price 15€. The quality is average. And the bread is under baked, white, too soft not crunchy. I usually don’t spend time to write negative review. I did this time because it isn’t correct to serve average quality for high price.\nIt deserves 2,5 stars.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A very well conceptualised food court with lots of of options. They have bars,burgers,Asian and Indian food. You can visit it before or after a movie as pathe gaumont is on the same building.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We came here to treat the kids to a morning of fun amidst a busy week of visits in Paris, lured by the prospect of lots of entertainment for them and a nice lunch in the food court. But when we got there, everything but the food court and the cinema was closed - apparently the kids activies won’t open before a couple of weeks. You would think that’s something worth mentioning on their website before having people trek all the way to La Villette for nothing! Yet another soulless place where the emphasis is making money. Such a let down.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Kind of expensive for the small size of the portions and low quality of the food. It's just pre-made industrial food reheated in a fancy microwave priced like a normal restaurant. Not worth it.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This review is for Pokke restaurant at Boom Boom villette. Very slow service and they mixed up with our order and gave it to another person. Waited 30 minutes for one bowl.', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Genki 元気
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious tea and bubble tea, and deserts to die for. The hot green jasmine tea with tapioca was so great for the cold winter of our visit to Paris.
The atmosphere has a nice sophisticated minimalist style and the service was very nice as well on both times that we visited.

They also serve Chinese food, but we didn’t have an opportunity to try it. Next time for sure! :)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This place is amazing. Very aesthetically pleasing as it is very minimalistic. Very luminous. The sitting is comfy and open. We ordered 4 different cakes and a drink : a basque cheesecake, a matcha mille crepe, an oreo and coconut cake, a mango cake and finally a mango frappé. They were all very tasty, the matcha mille crepe wasn’t too heavy nor sugary; the basque cheesecake is literally the best I found in Paris so far and not too sugary either. The mango cake is also light and flavourful. The oreo coco cake is the most sugary here and it was still very good. The drink was very refreshing even in this cold weather I would recommend. The service was very nice, the drinks are made in front of your eyes and the wait isn’t long at all. Owner very sweet and asks for advices on the cakes ! I recommend.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I order a strawberry cake and it was so tasty and fresh.
I took one star because the service is so slow.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "You won't regret trying this place.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I had the fraise cheese. The best strawberry boba that I've ever had in any country I've been to. Wennic Greeted me with a smile and kept that smile the whole time we were there.  Amazing service, amazing place.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Maison Louvard
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "The crookie stole the show during my recent visit. This trendy fusion of croissant and cookie proved to be a flavorful delight, though a bit pricey for its size. While I didn't explore beyond this famed treat, the bakery's array of tempting options suggests it's a spot worth revisiting for those with a sweet tooth 😋", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We called in for lunch and we were greeted by a very friendly waitress. We found the atmosphere to be excellent and very welcoming. Our waitress was very friendly and the food and service were superb. Braised beef cheek with seasonal vegetables and a terrine for starters were simply excellent. The wine was delicious too.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I tried the cookie croissant here few days ago. And it tastes as good as a regular croissant but 5 times more expensive, 7 times if you decide to take a table . Worth the hype? Not really.', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': '🤩 crookie whaaaaat! I’ve never had a cookie croissant 🥐 until today and I don’t think I can ever go back! Absolutely delicious, great cafe very vibrant and busy with lovely decor, perfect place to grab a morning coffee and treat!  As it’s quite popular service can be a bit slow but still well worth the visit', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I saw this bakery on Social Media and was curious to know why people were given such a high rate to this place. I wanted to check it by myself 😉 The place is cozy and well decorated. The staff is super friendly and the 'viennoiserie' tasteful. The expresso is also really good and compared to other places in the capital, your getting a decent amount of coffee in your cup (not only a few drops). It was good, but wouldn't given them a 5 star rate (even if the bakker has apparently received an award recently). Guess I will have to go a second time (at lunch) to confirm my thoughts... A place to recommend anyhow.", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Flam&go
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'The restaurant is great.
The portions are very big. We ended up splitting one formule between my friend and I (salted and sweet).
The food is very tasty we ordered Benedict eggs & Salmon with a brioche pain perdue. Both were amazing with fresh orange & coffee.
The service is good and the staff are very friendly. The place is colourful and very well decorated.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing place to eat a great brunch !
I celebrated my birthday over there, they were so sweet with me and my friends.

I highly recommend it !

Thank you for your kindness :)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good place', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent 👌', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I discovered this address yesterday and I am delighted with this moment. I opted for a brunch which, in addition to being very good, was plentiful. I was able to leave with the dessert which I was unable to finish. The atmosphere is a little noisy but it would be a shame to stop at that detail. I recommend !', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Pasticeria Simona
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'We found this place through "Paris food trip". Out of all the places we visited on the food trip, I think this was my favorite. Crazy Italian pastry shop in the middle of Paris. Love everything about it. From the pastry chef util the delicious cake we tasted.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Authentic Italian pastry, amazing coffee and a cozy atmosphere. Just perfection.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The cannolo was good, but I’ve tasted the best in Italy. Well, we’re in France not Italy, so can’t really compare. Since it’s called pasticceria, I was expecting bomboloni or donut but too bad there’s nothing like that. The cafe is small, only about 8 people max, however there are some seating outside. I would like to point out their hygiene, cz they serve the pastry with bare hands, no thongs whatsoever. We never know what did they touch before, especially that the pandemic is still there and another whatever disease around. Hopefully next time they take care more in hygiene part.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very delicious patisserie. She helped make my boyfriend a delicious personalized cake, thank you it was so good!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'One of the best places to find authentic Italian pastries!! Must try their Maritozzo and Biaocchi!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: KINGKONG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We tried a few dishes. Considering everything was prepared very quickly. Fried chicken wings were spicy buy had a very nice sweet glaze, super crunchy. Tteokbokki had interesting flavors, tasted like tajin but with extra spice. Bibimbap was good, but the sauce was very mild.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This restaurant is quite well hidden in a small street near metro station Strasbourg Saint-Denis. By the look of the exterior I probably wouldn’t have entered had I not checked Google reviews before… as the decor was somber and didn’t give an appetizing look to be honest.

However the food proved me wrong, we ordered lunch menu with the fried chicken as starter and bibimbap as main dish. The fried chicken was divine! So juicy and not greasy at all, the sweet and slightly spicy sauce blended perfectly with the batter, very delicious! The bibimbap itself was great too, it contained lots of ingredients especially vegetables, as they continued to cook in the stone ball they created a nice texture and taste together with the rice. I ordered the squid one, I should maybe have taken the beef and porc version as the squid was a bit chewy and not a lot of flavor. The other small negative point was probably that they were not very generous with the the pickled side dishes (see photo).

Overall I had a good dining experience and will definitely go back to try other dishes.

Update: we went back for the fried chicken and rice sticks, super delicious and you wouldn’t tell they were deep fried! Loved them.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really good place that serve authentic korean dishes!

Definitely a must take: the korean fried chicken, it was crispy and juicy.

Loved the kimchi fried rice with sea food, I would love to have some seaweed on it to be 100% matching with that I got in Korea!

Moreover great beer selection!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great place for late night eating or drinking, korean cuisine is not only about the bbq, kingkong is more like street style korean food with a nice atmosphere, kpop music and great customer service. The man (the owner maybe) was super friendly. Army stew was flavourful and very filling. I didn’t like the fried chicken very much, properly because of the sauce. The soft tofu stew (sundubu) is also average. All in all, great restaurant to try out and also their menu changes from time to time so it’s worth a comeback', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Unfortunately, they stopped serving their corndogs, but the food was delicious all the same! A nice Korean restaurant near Sentier, with a cool upstairs ambiance. Recommended!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Keopi
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Went there early and got a table. One can scan the QR code to see the menu with pictures. Great service and friendly staff. Definitely good place for brunch.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Delicious Korean brunch place! 🇰🇷\U0001faf6🏼
We had to wait just a little bit for a table inside. It’s located in a little alley, easy to find if using Google maps.

Small menu but with lots of options!
We got the fried chicken, which tasted just perfect! Very soft on the inside and the seasonings was on point.
Salmon toast and salmon waffle which were both delicious.
The orange juice was very fresh and sweet.
Service was super fast! Friendly staff.
And most importantly, everything is HALAL!
(Expect for one thing which is the “spam”)
Would definitely come back very soon!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'After watching their instagram account, I wanted to come here and try the brunch. It is an “instagramable” place, and as such, very popular so you’ll have to wait. However, the waiting times are less than expected and it is worth it. The food is great and innovative. I had the waffle with fried chicken and it was delicious and abundant. The fried chicken is perfect and the sauce (sweet and spice) too, although it is not spicy.
The only problem was the time they took to bring our beverages. We ordered the homemade lemonade and we were almost finishing the dish when they brought it. We noticed the service of beverages is slow, so be patient.
In any case, I’d love to come back to try the sweet options.

😋🌎🍽️✈️
Sabor Kairos', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for brunch at 11:30 on a Sunday and waited for half an hour to be seated cause it was quite crowded. It was worth the wait though cause the staff were nice, service was alright and the food was delicious. We had waffles and they placed a bottle of maple syrup on every table.  I had rose tea and my friends had matcha flavoured drinks and they were all good. Reservations are not possible so avoiding peak times would be a good idea.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The location is simply great, not too far from the Grevin museum ! You really get to feel the parisian vibe.
The price was reasonable for a brunch + it was really delicious. The staff is also really nice and attentive.
We went for a kimchi and avocado salmon toast (which if you like salty and spicy kimchi is a perfect match with avocado and salmon). The Rose Latte was too die for with its hint of rose taste. The spicy chicken was really soft (a perfect boneless chicken if I dare say).
And for the dessert the waffle with matcha cream ! The cream paired perfectly with the fruits and the waffle ~ Beware though, the plate is kind of big so if you don’t have a big appetite it is best to share it.

All in all the pricing, the amount of food and the taste was more than worthy, a 10/10 for me.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Trantranzai
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Loved the decor & environment of the restaurant! At the time we arrived (around 6:30pm) the grilled dumplings weren’t available unfortunately so we took the shrimp steamed ones. It was good but I think it would’ve been better grilled. In terms of noodles with soup, the portions are so big you are easily fulfilled ! Taste is good overall but the noodles were a bit dry even if it was in the soup. I would recommend though in terms of price/quantity/quality ratio it’s a win', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': '- Location is easy to access, walking distance to Metro & Bus stations.
- Nice service. It was quite busy at dinner.
- Noodles are excellent. The beef noodles are very tasty. The only point is that they serve with quite big amount.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "I love this atmosphere and design!!! It's not so often to see these decoration in China nowadays, but really have the feeling of walk into a film or go back to the last century. Food quality is top, i would recommend rice noodle.
. Service is perfect. Thank you and would come back again!!!", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Incredible Szechuan style noodles with authentic flavors. The atmosphere takes you straight to China, and we were seated very quickly despite the place being crowded. When you place your order, you can choose a spiciness level of 1-6. We ordered the beef noodles with level 4 spice, which was a perfect balance of flavor and spiciness. Service was on the slower side, but nothing to worry about.
Will definitely be visiting again.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "When you step into this Chinese restaurant in Paris, it's as if you've been instantly transported to China. The ambiance is authentic, and the food is not only delicious but also generously portioned. It's a culinary journey worth experiencing.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Land & monkeys
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "We felt so lucky to discover this vegan cafe chain in Paris. We had breakfast in a different branch for two days until we found our favourite one. The food is delicious (my boyfriend loves the monkey cookie!) and the presentation is enough to make you hungry, even if you've just eaten! All the staff we met speak English as well as French, which made ordering easy (although I did try to converse in French where possible). If I'm ever in Paris again, I'll definitely come back to this gem.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Best vegan bakery ever!! On our 3 day trip in Paris we went 3 times. That says it all!!😍\nWish they would open everywhere 👌🏼👌🏼✨def recommend :-)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Excellent vegan baked goods that look good and taste even better! Can't explain how good they are, surely wizardry is involved here. We loved everything we had, but the lemon tart was a favorite.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Excellent selection of vegan baked goods which were absolutely delicious. Outside seating area wasn't the nicest as the tables had bird poo on and there were lots of leaves and pigeon feathers on the floor. Also a few of the hot drinks from the menu were not in stock. I would come back though as the pastries were delicious. Great to see a completely vegan bakery!", 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'All vegan bakery!!!! Everything on the counter looked absolutely stunning! Great variety of sweet baked goods, sandwiches and the classic croissant and pain au chocolat which - both of them - were really delicious! Would definitely recommend!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Afri Call Food
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Food:
I tried mafe poulet with banane aloco, the rice was sticky and not well cooked, in the sauce always only the chicken and not vegetables. Banana was good.

Place:
Looks like fast food, I found it dirty with the floor sticking.

Tried once I don’t think I will go again', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent food. Balanced spices. Beautiful ingredients. Friendly service.  Best meal we had in paris', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really nice experience the food is good', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Super ! 10/10', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Super 👍', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Boneshaker Donuts
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'All donuts are vegan which is amazing. But they were too sweet and greasy for me :/ I normally like desserts but this donut was too much in terms of sugar.

Plus, most of the donuts are 6€ each which I think is a bit overpriced. I tried the raspberry donut on Saint Valentine’s day so it was in a heart shape (cute ^_^). Again I know that donut is not an healthy thing, but I wished that at least there would be some healthier maybe less greasy options.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'As a vegan, I was thrilled to find a place that sells vegan donuts in Paris. All of their donuts are made daily from scratch and in house too. I had to try their traditional glaze one and a seasonal fall flavored one that was apple pie inspired. I almost felt guilty eating these as they tasted so good. I would have ordered more had I had more time. Staff spoke English which was super helpful. They were also very kind and passionate about their food which I found very inspiring. A definite must go to if you want good donuts in general!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': '100% vegan. The donuts were amazing. The hot chocolate was OK. The cashier seemed like she was stressed out. The total for the items in the picture was about 33 euros.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Hands down, these are the best donuts in Paris. I’ve been coming here for years, and don’t plan on stopping anytime soon.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I am soo amazed that this place is vegan, you really can’t tell! The apple donut is autumn 🍂 in a donut ♥️ so fluffy and amazing flavour combo!

The owners also are very cute and kind!

Will be back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: OYA Fusion
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'It was not busy when we came. Service was excellent. Staff are quite attentive and pleasant. They seem to be joyful in serving people. The one serving our table likes to hum.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I think quality of food is average. I’ve like the starter (oeuf mollet), very disappointed by the desert though. I had a mango cheesecake. I think it was an industrial cheesecake. If not, it tasted like it was. Very heavy.

Good service though.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Best restaurant in town with best team 👍🏻
Thank you for perfect service since years.
Lovely regards from Germany and see you soon again', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing service, all staff were so welcoming and polite. Our waiter was so kind he read the menu out to us in English. Best burger we have ever had,  coktails went down a treat Try the rose bourbon for a sweet one.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Service on point and atmosphere just dope. Great DJ. I strongly recommend.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Café Louis Vuitton
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': "What a great place to sit after you have finished your visit at the Louis Vuitton Museum in a sunny but cold winter morning. The sweets are so beautiful, you just don't want to eat them. The place has a beautiful energy and atmosphere. Warm, though, with many windows and a great view of the river. The coffee is beautifully presented and the furniture is not too heavy. It is a really great place to visit as a continuation of a visit to the Louis Vuitton Museum, which is at the ground floor.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A great place to stop by after (or before) visiting the museum. A little overpriced but thats luxury brands for you haha, definitely worth a visit though. We went around 5:30pm on a Monday (early March) and we didn’t need to reserve or make a booking. The cakes and pastries were actually delicious and the staff were lovely.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'LV cafe was exceptionally good. I highly highly highly recommend making reservations. We made them for 12:30 pm and it wasn’t crowded and by the time we left at 3, there was at least 30 people waiting for a table. The food is not only beautiful, but so good. The eggs in particularly are really cool to try. And the desserts are so good. You can also do the LV dream experience after you eat!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent desserts and coffee!  Insanely overpriced?  Of course! What else would you expect.  Great service, great view out the windows at the Seine, and an unforgettable experience.  A must do after the Louvre or anytime!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Probably the most delicious cake I've ever ate! We got the chocolate and vanilla ones and they were amazing!\nPretty pricey, but understandable - it's Louis Vuitton!\nStaff was amazing, very friendly and very caring, smiling! Will definitely return when back in Paris", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: ACÀ PIGALLE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Definitely worth coming here. At first we thought food was going to suck since they microwave a lot of the dishes but it was one of the best meals. Taco meat was so tasty and their burrito was 5/5! Would love to come back here again!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for dinner without reservation, but even tho they were packed, they were able to give us a table.
We got a liter of margarita to go with our Acà nachos. They were crisp and the topping was guacamole, some pulled meat and cheddar. Overall very tasty and yummy.
For the entrees we got burritos with different meats, and all of them were up to our expectations. The portion was also good, didn’t leave anyone hungry.
The only thing we noticed was that it took some time to get the attention of the waiter to order the entrees, but they were really packed and everyone was running around, so it’s understandable.
Recommended if you are around the Moulin Rogue.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Authentic Mexican food.
Relaxed atmosphere with great music.
Service attentive and friendly.
Very popular place at lunchtime.
No reservations possible at this time. Here it is first come, first served!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Really nice Tacos, a bit disappointed with my cantarito, which was adapted to Paris, a bit bitter instead sour and sweet. It is an amazing drink, anyway that you should try citric, refreshing and their version bitter.  I loved my nachos and my governor tacos(prawn).
The horchata will be 100% better if you make it natural.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Overall, is a good place to eat tacos considering you are in Paris. Formule of three tacos for 10€ is a great option. Good flavor in the barbacoa, pastor a little dry, and carnitas would improve with a little more coriander. Sauces are good and tasty, not super spicy. Agua de horchata is super good, not too sweat which I like.  However, the dessert, the pastel de tres leches, falls short of expectations. While sweet and pastry-like, it lacks the authentic essence of a true pastel de tres leches.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Maison Maé
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'My favourite bakery in Paris. My everyday breakfast was here during my trip. The croissants are the best. And the apple pies are the best of the best. The jam in the pie is so good, not too sour, not too sweet. Everything is just fine. The owners are really nice people also. One nice lady, with two handsome boys. Wish i could take everything here with me back to Shanghai.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I came for breakfast all three mornings that I stayed in Paris and I must say that I could not have found anything better. From the friendly and lovable staff (who even gave me a croissant on the last day when they saw me with my luggage) to the pastries that were simply delicious.
I will definitely return when I have the opportunity to revisit the city.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This is a really nice local coffee place with fresh bakery and desserts. The lovely staff is very helpful and friendly who doesnt mind go the extra mile to help a customer. Everything in the menu is priceful here.
The welcoming smile from them, with the tasteful croissants/pastries and quality hot coffees and the small but warm atmosphere is an obvious five star rate.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing croissants, pain au chocolat is to die for… loving this bakery and the hosts are very lovely and pleasant 🤗🤗🤗
We recommend it with our hearts ☺️', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'My 3 friends and I are visiting Paris as Americans for the first time and this cafe is the most amazing part of Paris. Friendly staff, who have been helping us with our French, tasty food at a reasonable price, and a relaxing atmosphere. We’ve come here every morning and will definitely come again the next time we visit! I’d recommend the ham escargot and the espresso! They also gave our group free pastries sometimes :)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Puffy Cookies
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Best cookies I’ve tried in Paris (and I’m extremely fussy with my cookies). They’re perfectly soft in the middle and ‘mi-cuit’. They’re very balanced, not too sweet, the chocolate feels like it’s nice quality and same for the nuts that they use that are perfectly toasted and crunchy which gives a more interesting texture to the cookies. Can feel they put a bit of salt in the cookies which I appreciate. They definitely don’t taste like fake vanilla. Very very generously sized and I love all their branding! I think the posters inside are really well done. My favourite cookie was the chocolate and hazelnut one. My boyfriend’s favourite was the dark chocolate one!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Do you wanna try the best cookies in Paris??? Run here. Perfectly soft on the inside. Wide range of options. Prices are decent. Open every day. Perfect.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The best cookies in Paris!

These cookies are gooey and soft but yet still crunchy on the outside.

The staff were very nice and gave recommendations. The cookies are a bit more than your average cookie but it is worth it.

I paid 7.50€ for two cookies.

If you’re visiting Paris definitely make a trip to get these cookies!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Cookies are to die for (levain bakery NYC style!) coffee really good, and milkshake is a killer 🤤 plus the service is super friendly, and you have some inside space to enjoy your calories intake', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This is not a normal cookie, it’s thick and gooey. The chocolate and peanut butter one was my favourite.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Kous
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'This "bar" is a take-away for couscous.
The choice of vegetables and meats is wide and the quality excellent.
However, like everything in Paris the prices are relatively steep.
For 3 persons, couscous with mixed meats, will cost about 45 Euro.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Marocco food is amazing and also cheap for size M €14 u can share also( I’m Asian so for me the portion is quite big );) it’s good for health and diet. Recommend place for lunch', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very tasty and fast couscous at a reasonable price! The lamb one (Tanjia) in particular is delicious! Perfect place for lunch breaks', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'They have been their for over 6 years worth a visit!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This place was THE BEST! I met the owner Bader and he was super nice. A must try if you’re in Paris!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Taco Mesa
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'The food was incredible not only in taste but also in aesthetics. The freshness of the ingredients is unmistakable, and the proportions were just right. Tommy’s margarita and the churros are also a must try! If you miss authentic Mexican cuisine, this is definitely the place to go.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'great atmosphere. came with a friend who knows mexican food. good portion of meat for al pastor & great flavour for quesadilla.\nprice for 3 tacos and a drink wasn’t cheap. took some time to wait for all three dishes since it got quite popular during peak hours.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Authentic Mexican food.  Freshly made tortillas. My vegetarian tacos were very tasty and my daughter's birria tacos also great. The churros were superb. A little expensive but definitely will recommend.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I’m from California and was craving tacos so we went here and I’m so glad we did! Their Paloma and tacos were so good. I loved them all, especially the Birria one. Great service!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'BEST Tacos in Paris 🌮!!taste and feel like Mexico!! 🇲🇽 SOOOO good', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: GYOZA HOUSE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Most creative gyozas I tried in Paris.
Truly a wonderful cuisine served near Opera. It is this kind of dish which gives you a happy day! It’s also affordable given the quality which you get.
Highly highly recommend to go.
I recommend the shiitake veggie gyoza which will make you melt ✨', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved the food and the wide selection. Great presentation, atmosphere, decoration and eating experience. However difficult to see the difference of which flavor gyoza was which when served. Music choice was very pleasant.
There were unfortunately  two flickering lights which was distracting.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very good gyozas and lots of choices. Super friendly staff and cute setting.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Gyoza 🥟 coconut chicken filling was good.  If you are from East Asia, you probably won't be satisfied by some of the taste, however, It's quite interesting to try 8 flavour gyoza in one go 😊", 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'For me, it’s easy. If you feel like eating gyozas, you need to come to this place.

It’s the best gyozas you can find in the city.

The service is nice and very polite.

You won’t be disappointed. I highly recommend.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: CHEZ HAKI
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "Went with my girlfriend; we enjoyed the ravioli and Nems starters, both worth trying.

Unfortunately, the main dishes fell short. The Poulet Croustillant noodles lacked flavor, were excessively greasy, and the chicken was merely okay.

Riz loc-lac had dry rice, chewy beef, mainly fat.

Hoping to give the benefit of the doubt, we visited at 4 PM, but suspect the dishes weren't freshly made—microwave sounds and quick service raised concerns.", 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Good overall, good quality-price ratio, vegetarian lamen did not reach the highest expectations (noodles were very good, the broth could have a bit more flavor), but very large portion size, and definitely better than a lot of places in France.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We discovered this restaurant while on a walk and decided to try right then and there. The gyoza was fab and we also enjoyed the soup ramen. I ordered the fried chicken cutlet noodles for myself but the serving was pretty big and would actually be enough for two people. We shall return.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very busy Chinese restaurant with nice expedite staff and extremely fast turnaround. Food was good and overall a very authentic Chinese restaurant experience.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The food was incredible. Tender noodles with the perfect chew with rich delicious broth. We loved the S7! The service was excellent and the atmosphere cozy. A perfect rich and hearty meal at very reasonable prices especially for the flavor, portions, and quality.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Kous
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'I happened to stop by this place by coincidence and I am happy I did. The place is small and the food is good. I tried the Tanjia couscous and I did love it. This is important as I am not a couscous person by default and hate the exaggerated spices or the pool of liquids on my food. The staff are polite and attentive.

What caught my eye was the level of anticipations to the needs of clients

1- You can chose size of your plate, depending how hungry you are.

2- for first time I saw in my life that a restaurant also includes feminine hygiene pad also in the toilet.

Bravo for that , a good customer service wins .

I do recommend the place for those whom like to have a nice healthy food. I will eat there again while am in Paris.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Excellent couscous!  Several offerings. Vegetarian, meats, vegan. Choices of classic or whole wheat grain (couscous). Super fresh. Delicious mint tea & small North African pastries. Friendly service. Lovely setting in a modern North African style. Try it. You will not regret it.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "We're always a fan of Morrocan cuisine, and KOUS did not disappoint. Try the soup before your main dish, and get a cup of hot tea - you'll be glad you did.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A very pleasant place to eat a good, satisfying couscous, delicious mint tea and pastry and very tasty appetizer. The staff is very welcoming and obliging. I will definitely go back.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'So good', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Bao Express
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'If you looking for the correct style of food. Sorry, it is not. Fancy enough but nothing related to the food.

Their service was super quick, my dishes were delivered within 5 minutes after my order. All the food were cold when they arrivd my table.

Not tasty enough. The bun meat was dry and small portion, which a qualified meat bun shoul be meaty with juice. This style Chinese food should serve in hot and not pre cook.

At last, I am questioning about how the meat bun was made. You can saw that the bamboo steamer was dry compared to the Siumai one. The Siumai steamer was wet that mean at least the Siumai was steamed in it. Anyway, it was only my observation but mean nothing.', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I loved this place! In two weeks took the following: Chinese spring rolls (they were ok), Xiao Long Bao Shangai classic (the filling is very good and the dough is thick and fluffy), Char Siu Bao (basically the big dumplings, they are super tasty, I preferred these to the smaller ones), Aubergines Hong Shao (for sure the best thing we ate, they were delicious, I sincerely recommend these) and finally the Poulet Sweet & Sour (very good as well). We were very hungry and in the end we were quite full. Plus, the service was super kind and welcoming.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Very very overrated, you can find better asian
restaurants in Paris. Never order the lemonade, it is just water. The mango sago is a mango lassi with very few tapioca perles and some small chunks of mango. Aubergines and noodles are ok.
Service was great. A shame that food wasn’t as good. Everything is deeply fried.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved this great place. 😋
Great food, options even for vegans.
Big place so you can be spontaneous, friendly staff.
Enjoy', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'This has to be one of THE HIDDEN GEMS of Paris. This isn’t on any tourist lists of places to eat and it’s not typical French food, but it is delicious and the vibe in this place is immaculate. We enjoyed it so much, we went back on our last night in Paris to have it again!  Beef Ho Fun is easily the best dish we had in Paris and the Sweet and Sour Chicken is unlike any version we’ve had in the best way possible. Also, if you’re a dessert person, the lava French toast is a must try!  We would eat here again and again and will recommend this place to anyone traveling to Paris!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: RAMEN WANG
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': "This is the most delicious ramen I have ever tasted in Paris. It reminds me of the ramen in Tokyo that I missed so much. Fast service, polite staff. Clean and comfortable. There may be a line outside, but it's worth the wait. I'm glad I found this place", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing place! Very good food and good service and fair prices. Every Tuesday they have vegan ramen. Would definitely come back', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I’ve had ramen in Hong Kong and Tokyo and this is definitely one of my favourites of all time. We’ve been several times, at different times of the day and days of the week yet the food has been amazingly consistent every single time.

The pork is their speciality and spectacular, every bite makes me so happy. The soup is always flavoursome and balanced.

Unfortunately they don’t take booking in advance so you have to queue. One time we went with our friends (~about 8 of us in total) after our wedding and we had to wait a long time as there was a lot of us but as the food was so tasty, people forgot about the long wait.

All of the staff are friendly, wonderful and attentive and it’s always a pleasure to come here.

While it’s growing in popularity, I hope it’ll stay consistent and continue to be a gem in the 14th arrondissement.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Loved to eat with you. Just needed to wait some minutes outside. But was worth it!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Everything was delicious! Ramen was amazing with lots of flavors. The veggie gyozas as appetizers were tasty too. Nice variety of desserts and I really recommend the matcha financiers with ginger ice cream. Nice wine by the glass as well. Very cozy venue and ambience. A must!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: LiBeyrouth
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'I have no complaints about the taste of the food, but I feel it is overpriced for the range of items we get there I have been to few Indian buffets which offer a huge range of items when compared to this with the same price. We waited for 15 mins I guess just to get in and the place was very compact. I even had to wait to refill my plate. The toilet was extremely untidy, with no toilet paper and hand wash. "Please at least keep your toilet clean for customers my sincere request to you".', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Within four years, I have eaten here four times. As always, a dream! Simple Lebanese dishes prepared with love. My favorite is parsley salad with tomatoes and eggplant salad! Chicken is also seasoned great! Everything tastes good! Small but nice. You must also try the Lebanese beer. The guys are very nice and ready to explain everything! Thank you, I will come back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "😋Very effective Lebanese all you can eat buffet with tasty dishes. The selection is small but well prepared, there is a cold and warm selection. Their cuisine is fresh and full of flavor.

⚠️The place is popular so it gets crowded easily with a waiting queue outside in the evening !

😕 The downsides :
- Toilets are on the outside, so if its rainy its not rly convenient..
- The limited space : they dont take reservations so forget it if you're planning to be in a group bigger than 4 people unless you're willing to wait a lot outside.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The staff is very friendly and the food was very good. We had the chance to taste every plate and all of them was tasty.
We paid 19,99 for a “All you can eat”.

We also had tea and desert. They were also very nice.

I completely recommend this restaurant.

Also, make sure to come early otherwise you will queue for a long time. (We waited 1h).', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We went for the 20€ buffet and there was a long queue but we decided to wait. We got seated in a bit of a tight space but the Lebanese staff were super friendly and welcoming and offered us drinks and desserts. The food was also of high quality, and overall, it was a nice experience. Would definitely recommend, worth the wait.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Mopa
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Awesome vegan place with really filling and tasty food! We tried the arancini, cold beast burger, and doner kebab. The portions were very filling and the flavors were incredible. Can’t wait to come back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Very nice place with friendly staff and tasty food. Can't wait to try the brunch!", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Really atmospheric vegan place –\xa0I docked a star because the burger was good, but not the most amazing vegan burger ever. Good fries, friendly staff – but lots of stuff wasn't available from menu on a Saturday night.", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "The service and interaction alone with the server was top notch. He even gave me a charger to top up my battery. I instantly felt welcome in this small but cosy environment. I didn't know how to eat my Kebap initially but once I figured out my technique, it was a sumptuous mix of soft bread filled with awesome delicacies.\nThe cheesecake was the perfect way to end this beautiful meal which I accompanied with a chai latte. Mind you, Mopa are not big on sugar, which is perfect for me but not to everyone's taste, so do ask whether any supposed sweet item you order has sugar in it already.\nHighly recommended whenever you visit Paris or just want to try something different. The nuggets will freak you out, so lookout to be blown away. Okay. Enjoy.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great little vegan place. Food was very tasty, service was brilliant. We had the cheeseburger, bacon burger and Berliner kebap with fries. Good came quickly, not greasy at all. Red wine was a good accompaniment!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Maslow - Restaurant Paris 1
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'Been wanting to go for ages now and so glad we went ! Lovely vibes, lovely and quite big , airy restaurant that is relaxed yet professional, friendly service. Boyfriend and I took the fixed lunch menu at 19 euros. His œuf parfaits with brioche was absolutely delicious and my vegetarian donburi dish( breaded mushroom) was good but not outstanding . The choux à la crème ( caramelized puff pastry with  salted caramel and cream center hit the spot and the coffee was fine . We will be back 🙏🌸', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Out of my Michelin Stars Challenges (follow me for all the reviews on every Michelin Stars in Paris and more… way more), I try non Michelin but mainly veggie places thanks to a good friend who is vegetarian. It’s a good hack to go in friendly up and coming places.\nThis one is no exception. Very busy, very lively. The service is super nice. The food is fun. Granted it’s not a star, but it’s fun. The sound level due to the design is quite high (especially compared to my usual Michelin star…) but it’s the price to pay to go in a very lively place.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "We arrived after seeing its great reviews but not realizing it was a vegetarian restaurant.  They asked if we had reservations, we didn't, but they still accommodated us.  We ordered the squash (my favorite) the cauliflower wings (my friends favorite) and the gnocchi (mushroom forward and delicious).  I also tried the BSA mocktail. A delicious and refreshing lemon tart drink that went very well with the meal.  As someone who wouldn't normally seek a vegetarian restaurant, I left feeling very satisfied and full and I'm still craving more of that incredible squash.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'The place is really chic and has a great vibe. The service is a 10/10.\nThe food failed to impress me. It was fresh and tasty but for the portion size, you end up paying a premium. The small plates are very small. The main has only two options and one of it has eggs.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Best meal in Paris by far. Kid approved as well! The service, ambience and food quality was superb. Our waiter Alex was so kind and attentive. He made just the perfect recommendations. We are looking forward to coming back! Merci beaucoup!!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Jungle Palace
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Overall the experience is good!

We came here for the theme, and it delivers!

We were serviced by Agathe, she is very nice! Quick and friendly service was offer and she is very responsive towards our requests.

The food portion is smaller than expected, the taco that we ordered turns out only have two pieces.

Veggie curry feels too simple since it mainly consists two types of veggie. It would be great if more varieties are offered.

The fish were really cool.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'A different culinary experience with music, sounds and special effects. The food is good value for money, the staff is young and friendly. Portions a bit small. Entrance is possible for people with reduced mobility but the toilet is on the top floor, with stairs. Very original and worth a visit!', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Wow just wow! The ambiance, food, drinks, dessert, service, cleanliness, and experience was phenomenal. Highly recommend!!! The Gorilla Mule was my favorite drink but they were all good. The chicken skewers and the shrimp curry were delicious! We also had the Banana chocolate dessert and it was so good. Our server was so kind and very attentive too.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Great experience and excellent setting. Food was amazing !
Overall the staff was great  ( warm welcome and friendly ) except for one female waitress who wasn’t friendly at all and looked annoyed the entire evening. Thankfully her colleague was funny and a great contrast ! )', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Def must visit , loved the ambience and the Pulled Pork Burger was amazing .also recommend the eggplant for starter !!! The Banoffee desert was lovely and light and we all enjoyed the whole experience.
Service was super attentive and smiling all the time , making our visit memorable. Dishes were well explained to us as well. In particular, our waitress named Aure was very sweet and knows her job to a tee.

Only comment for restaurant was that at some point the music was a little repetitive. But didn't bother me that much but just something to consider", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Marcus Pizze Amore
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'My favorite Pizzeria. This Pizzeria has a lot of vegan options which makes it perfect when I’m looking for a place to go with my friends. They even have delicious vegan dessert options (vegan Tiramisù, vegan Nocciola Calzone and vegan Pizza bread sticks with Nocciola 🤤).

This time I had a vegan Margherita and the Pizza sticks with Nocciola as take away for lunch. It tasted great as always and the team was super friendly.

I really like how the place looks like. It is small and cosy. Definitely great to eat there. It gets packed quickly so come early if you want to be sure to get a table! 😄', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Went here for lunch and have no regrets. It’s one of the best pizzas, let alone vegan pizzas, I’ve ever had. My brother also loved his margarita pizza.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Definitely the best vegan pizza in Paris. Some of the best I've tried anywhere in the world, actually! They need to open an all-vegan restaurant!!", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "The pizza was great & the people even better, i personally enjoyed the 'Tortufo' vegan pizza which was totally incredible & girlfriend had a margarita which also was delicious.

I'd recommend going with vegan pizza! 👍👍", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Super friendly staff and AMAZING vegan pizza. The vegan tiramisu was also amazing. Would 10/10 eat here again!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: La Piadineria
reviews: [{'author': '', 'text': 'I am almost sure those reviews are fake. The food was absolutely horrible 0 flavors and 0 relation to italy. If i buy jambon and make a sandwich at home it will be 10 times more delicious and cheaper. Its a scam', 'rating': '1', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'I guess it was alright. I ordered online the day before but when I came my order wasn’t ready so it was a bit frustrating. I chose the Ortolana with fries. It was ok it wasn’t really tasty, the goat cheese’s was all that was to it. It was quite flat and unsatisfying.\nBut if you want something quick enough to eat then you can come here it’s alright and quite cheap.', 'rating': '3', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'GREAT FOOD. As an Italian, the food was just as back home. Super recommended!!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We got the student menu! It was very tasty', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing service! Very friendly and welcoming!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Plan D - DWICH & GLACE
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'Yeah, it’s a stone cold 5 stars. Incredible food, location is great, you can easily sit beside the canal and eat (since it’s really a tiny bar set up inside), prices super reasonable, staff were friendly and have superhuman memory for who ordered what. One note: it’s popular and busy, so plan to queue and wait for food. Totally worth it tho.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'We came by for lunch. this is a tiny deli type restaurant. You only have a bar to sit. Menu consists of two sandwiches and 2 sides and desserts. I think it regularly changes. We took the mushroom sandwich (le brun), fries, and salad with sesame vinaigrette sauce. Honestly everything was perfect. The sandwich was phenomenal. Also unrelated maybe but everyone working there that day was super beautiful/handsome so both your stomach and your eyes have a feast 👉🏻👈🏻😌', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'BEST PLACE ON EARTH.
I am not kidding, I think I go there at lease once a month. They make the tastiest, most flavorful sandwiches you’ll ever have. And everything is vegan. They are politically, ethically, socially engaged. The staff is the nicest.
Sandwich choices are a rotation of 2 seasonal recipes.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': 'Amazing sandwiches and lovely staff. Simple but very effective concept. Haven’t stopped thinking about that purple sandwich since yesterday. Could not recommend more.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Plan D is a haven for vegetarian/vegan sandwich enthusiasts.
It's a blast to find a place where you can eat vegan without feeling like you're left with the side dish. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a delicious and satisfying experience that leaves a lasting impression.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}]

name: Green Farmer's Paris
reviews:
[{'author': '', 'text': 'We got takeaway here and I was super impressed with all the food. The burgers were juicy and more ish, the nuggets had a great crisp and the fish n chips was a massive portion. The Smash Truffle really stood out, such a great flavour. I really enjoyed it and would love to go back and eat in the restaurant too!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': None, 'author_profile_url': '', 'lang': ''}, {'author': '', 'text': "Staff was very nice (spoke some English which was super helpful understanding the menu). Inside is kind of small but still enough seating and some outside of a busy street. The food was pretty tasty. I wasn't a big fan of the sauces they made in house, but they have a wide range of them for you to try. Also tried one of their canned beverages. Again not the biggest fan but if you like soda I think you will like.
